
1. 飲茶  
廣東話：今朝同屋企人去飲茶，叫咗蝦餃同燒賣。  
English: I went for yum cha with my family this morning and ordered har gow and siu mai.  

2. 圖書館  
廣東話：我成日去圖書館溫書，因為嗰度好靜。  
English: I often go to the library to study because it's very quiet there.  

3. 養聲  
廣東話：佢係歌手，所以好注重養聲，唔會亂咁嗌。  
English: He is a singer, so he takes good care of his voice and avoids shouting.  

4. 票尾  
廣東話：入場嘅時候記得留起票尾，可能有抽獎。  
English: Remember to keep the ticket stub when entering, as there might be a lottery.  

5. hacker  
廣東話：個hacker入侵咗公司嘅系統，偷走咗啲資料。  
English: The hacker breached the company's system and stole some data.  

6. 石斛蘭  
廣東話：我喺花市買咗盆石斛蘭，佢可以掛喺樹度生。  
English: I bought a dendrobium orchid at the flower market; it can grow attached to trees.  

7. 吊詭  
廣東話：呢個情況真係好吊詭，明明係幫佢但佢反而嬲咗。  
English: This situation is really paradoxical; I was helping him but he got angry instead.  

8. 吊詭  
廣東話：佢講嘅道理聽落吊詭，但其實好有智慧。  
English: What he said sounds absurd, but it's actually very wise.  

9. 各為其主  
廣東話：戰場上兩兄弟各為其主，唯有兵戎相見。  
English: On the battlefield, the two brothers fought for their respective masters and had to confront each other.  

10. 軨蓋  
廣東話：架車個軨蓋花咗，要拎去整一整。  
English: The car's wheel cover is scratched and needs to be repaired.  

11. 打哥夫  
廣東話：禮拜日約咗班同事去打哥夫。  
English: I made plans with colleagues to play golf on Sunday.  

12. 免揀  
廣東話：呢啲生果係免揀嘅，一兜賣晒唔俾揀。  
English: These fruits are sold without selection; the whole basket is sold without picking.  

13. 擺闊佬  
廣東話：佢成日擺闊佬，其實銀行戶口得個吉。  
English: He always shows off his wealth, but his bank account is actually empty.  

14. 廣播劇  
廣東話：我細個好鍾意聽電台播嘅廣播劇。  
English: I loved listening to radio dramas when I was young.  

15. 錄影機  
廣東話：以前追劇要靠錄影機錄低嚟睇。  
English: In the past, we relied on VCRs to record shows for later viewing.  

16. 吟詩吟唔甩  
廣東話：今次證據確鑿，你真係吟詩吟唔甩喇。  
English: The evidence is solid this time; you really can't deny it.  

17. 佈道大會  
廣東話：教會今個周末會舉辦佈道大會。  
English: The church is holding a preaching rally this weekend.  

18. 寫手  
廣東話：佢係報館嘅寫手，專門寫社論。  
English: He is a writer for the newspaper, specializing in editorials.  

19. 寫手  
廣東話：呢篇文章搵咗代筆寫手，唔係作者自己寫。  
English: This article was written by a ghostwriter, not the author himself.  

20. 代打  
廣東話：我個仔打機唔得，成日要搵人代打。  
English: My son is not good at gaming and often needs someone to play for him.  

21. 茶碗  
廣東話：日本茶道要用特定嘅茶碗嚟飲抹茶。  
English: Japanese tea ceremony requires specific chawan bowls for drinking matcha.  

22. 茶隔  
廣東話：沖普洱茶最好用茶隔，唔使食到茶葉。  
English: It's best to use a tea strainer when brewing pu-erh tea to avoid drinking the leaves.  

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈  
廣東話：公司高層遲到冇事，我哋遲一分鐘就扣錢，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈！  
English: Management can be late without consequences, but we get docked pay for being one minute late—it's pure hypocrisy!  

24. 獨唱  
廣東話：今晚嘅表演佢會獨唱一首經典金曲。  
English: He will perform a classic song solo in tonight's show.  

25. 快人快事  
廣東話：佢做事一向快人快事，唔會拖拖拉拉。  
English: He always handles things quickly and efficiently without delay.  

26. 四腳獸  
廣東話：有人話喺商場廁所見到四腳獸，唔知真定假。  
English: Someone claimed they saw a "four-legged beast" in the mall restroom—not sure if it's true.  

27. 無米粥  
廣東話：傾咗成個月都係煲無米粥，根本冇實際進展。  
English: We've been discussing for a month with no real progress—it's all just preliminary talk.  

28. 義會  
廣東話：舊時阿媽會參加義會，幫補吓屋企開支。  
English: In the past, my mother joined mutual aid associations to help with household expenses.  

29. 榜文  
廣東話：古代嘅榜文會貼喺城門，等百姓知悉官府消息。  
English: In ancient times, official notices were posted on city gates for the public to see.  

30. MK名  
廣東話：佢個MK名改到花哩花碌，仲加咗個「唯愛」字頭。  
English: His MK-style online name is overly flashy with a "唯愛" (only love) prefix. [end of text]


